      "locked": false,
      "text": "Scenario\n\nYou are responsible for a centralized platform service used by multiple internal product teams across the company.\n\nThe platform’s job is to approve or block irreversible actions that have external, real-world impact—for example:\n        •        triggering customer communications,\n        •        releasing funds,\n        •        publishing regulated data,\n        •        executing automated remediation actions,\n        •        or activating large-scale experiments.\n\nRecently, the company experienced a high-impact incident:\n        •        An automated workflow executed an irreversible action at scale.\n        •        The action was technically valid but contextually wrong (bad timing, stale signal, missing approval).\n        •        The blast radius was large enough to trigger legal review, executive escalation, and regulator notification.\n\nAs a result, leadership wants a platform-level safety system that sits in front of these actions.\n\nConstraints (non-negotiable)\n        •        Actions may be initiated by humans, automation, or AI agents\n        •        Some actions must complete in under 500ms end-to-end\n        •        The system must support explicit executive overrides\n        •        Every decision must be auditable months later\n        •        The company operates in multiple regions with different regulatory expectations\n        •        This platform must not become a single point of failure that blocks the business indefinitely\n\nTension you must resolve\n        •        Move fast without creating irreversible damage\n        •        Allow overrides without destroying trust in the system\n        •        Enforce safety without turning into a human bottleneck",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Scenario\n\nYou are responsible for a centralized platform service used by multiple internal product teams across the company.\n\nThe platform’s job is to approve or block irreversible actions that have external, real-world impact—for example:\n        •        triggering customer communications,\n        •        releasing funds,\n        •        publishing regulated data,\n        •        executing automated remediation actions,\n        •        or activating large-scale experiments.\n\nRecently, the company experienced a high-impact incident:\n        •        An automated workflow executed an irreversible action at scale.\n        •        The action was technically valid but contextually wrong (bad timing, stale signal, missing approval).\n        •        The blast radius was large enough to trigger legal review, executive escalation, and regulator notification.\n\nAs a result, leadership wants a platform-level safety system that sits in front of these actions.\n\nConstraints (non-negotiable)\n        •        Actions may be initiated by humans, automation, or AI agents\n        •        Some actions must complete in under 500ms end-to-end\n        •        The system must support explicit executive overrides\n        •        Every decision must be auditable months later\n        •        The company operates in multiple regions with different regulatory expectations\n        •        This platform must not become a single point of failure that blocks the business indefinitely\n\nTension you must resolve\n        •        Move fast without creating irreversible damage\n        •        Allow overrides without destroying trust in the system\n        •        Enforce safety without turning into a human bottleneck",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
